markets.title: Will Biden's approval rating ever get below 38% by Mar 31, 2024?
markets.rules_primary: If, according to FiveThirtyEight, Biden's minimum approval rating is below 38 between Issuance and Mar 31, 2024, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
PLEASE NOTE:  the values considered are only the values for each day as checked at 10:00 AM ET after that day has finished. Intra-day values are not considered. For example, if for a given day the 538 Approval rating for the President hits 45.0% and ten minutes later falls back to 44.6% and stays at 44.6% through the end of the day, then the 45.0% will not be considered for purposes of calculating the minimum or maximum.

Changes following the first 10:00 AM ET after a given date are not included in consideration. For example, if a methodology change makes it so that the approval rating two weeks prior to yesterday fell below or above a given threshold, it would not push markets with that threshold to YES. Only the value for the date at the first 10:00 AM ET after the date is considered.
markets.early_close_condition: If this event occurs, the market will close the following 10am ET.
